{{Infobox person | name = Fabio Zerpa | image =Fabio Zerpa.jpg | caption =Zerpa in 1969 | birth_name = Fabio Zerpa | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1928|12|4}} | birth_place = [[Rosario, Uruguay]] | occupation = [[Ufologist]], [[writer]], [[historian]], [[parapsychologist]] | nationality =[[Uruguay]]an | Died = | Affiliates = | URL = [http://www.fabiozerpa.com.ar Fabio Zerpa] |}}
'''Fabio Zerpa''' (born in [[Rosario, Uruguay|Rosario]], [[Uruguay]])<ref name="cine">{{cite web|url=http://www.cinenacional.com/personas/index.php?persona=7418|title=Fabio Zerpa's filmography|author=|date=|work=|publisher=cinenacional.com|accessdate=4 May 2011|language=es}}</ref> is an actor, [[parapsychologist]] and [[ufology|UFO researcher]]. He resides in [[Argentina]] since 1951.<ref name=FZERPA>{{cite web| title = UFO INFO: "Argentina: Ufologist to Visit Policeman in Disappearance Case." (Fabio Zerpa) |url=http://www.ufoinfo.com/news/argentinapoliceman3.shtml | accessdate = 2008-02-05}}</ref>
==Biography== Fabio Zerpa arrived in [[Argentina]] in 1951. Following a short theatrical career,<ref>[http://www.fabiozerpa.com.ar/fabiozerpa/zerpa_cvartistico.html#.UZ6dxaK55XE Quién es Fabio Zerpa] from Fabio Zerpa official website</ref> he became increasingly interested in [[extraterrestrial life]], having already studied [[psychology]]. After some years of investigation, Zerpa started to give his first conferences at the beginning of the 1960s. In 1966 he created the radio program ''Más allá de la cuarta dimensión'' (Beyond the Fourth Dimension). Since then, Fabio Zerpa has reported on more than 3,000 cases of UFO sightings and contact with [[extraterrestrials]]. Since 2001 he has been the director of the on-line magazine ''[[El Quinto Hombre]]'' (The Fifth Man). In December 2005 Zerpa was appointed cultural ambassador of the city of [[Colonia, Uruguay|Colonia]], in his native country.
