{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}} {{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox person | name = Madhuri Bhattacharya | image = MadhuriBhattacharya.jpg | alt = | caption = Madhuri Bhattacharya in 2010 | birth_date = 1 July 1982 (age 35) | birth_place = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], [[India]] | other_names = | occupation = Model, actress }}
'''Madhuri Bhattacharya''' is an Indian actress and former model, who has appeared in [[Kannada cinema|Kannada]] and [[Bollywood]] films.
==Early life== Born in Bangalore in a [[Bengali people|Bengali]] family, Bhattacharya studied at the [[Indian Army Public Schools|Army Public School]] and later went to [[Mount Carmel College, Bangalore|Mount Carmel College]] to study psychology and Ramaiah College to study law.<ref>{{cite web|title=Biography of Madhuri Bhattacharya|url=http://www.gomolo.in/People/PeopleBiographyUser.aspx?pplid=7869&bioID=1118678|publisher=Gomolo.in|accessdate=17 March 2011|date=25 March 2010}}</ref> She lived in [[R.T. Nagar]], [[Bangalore]] with her parents, before moving to [[Mumbai]] to pursue modelling.<ref>{{cite news|title=Game on|url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article258132.ece|work=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=15 March 2011|author=Shilpa Sebastian R.|location=Chennai, India|date=19 March 2010}}</ref> She won several beauty contests including the Miss Bangalore title before embarking on her film career.<ref>{{cite news|title=Madhuri is ready to play!|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-01-24/news-interviews/28125770_1_madhuri-dixit-kheny-s-prem-kaa-game-ashok-kheny-s-prem-kaa| work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=17 March 2011|date=24 January 2010}}</ref>
==Career== Bhattacharya started her film career by appearing in the [[Kannada]] films ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]'' and ''Bisi Bisi''. She also modelled for two videos of [[Sonu Nigam]] from his album ''[[Neene Bari Neene]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arbaaz is a dear friend: Madhuri|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-08-21/news-interviews/28153500_1_kannada-film-arbaaz-khan-madhuri-bhattacharya|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=17 March 2011|date=21 August 2009}}</ref> She acted in [[Sahara One]]'s television series ''[[Kuchh Love Kuchh Masti]]'' which was the Indian adaptation of the popular series ''[[Sex and the City]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Unfazed by rumours|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/60290/unfazed-rumours.html |work=[[Deccan Herald]] |accessdate=17 March 2011 |author=Nina C George}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Awesome threesome|url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2004/11/16/stories/2004111600280400.htm|work=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=17 March 2011|date=16 November 2004|location=Chennai, India}}</ref> In 2009, she appeared in two Bollywood films, ''Bachelor Party'' and ''3 Nights 4 Days''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Madhuri Bhattacharya: Filmography|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/filmography/19482/index.html|publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|accessdate=17 March 2011}}</ref> Her first full fledge role came in the 2010 [[comedy film|comedy]], ''[[Prem Kaa Game]]'' alongside [[Arbaaz Khan (Indian actor)|Arbaaz Khan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Meet the girl who plays Prem Ka Game |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/features/2009/05/01/5168/index.html |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |accessdate=17 March 2011 |date=1 May 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100519114315/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/features/2009/05/01/5168/index.html |archivedate=19 May 2010 }}</ref> In 2011, she featured in the popular item song "Tinku Jiya" alongside [[Dharmendra]] and [[Bobby Deol]] in the film ''[[Yamla Pagla Deewana]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Madhuri magic on the Deols|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-11/news-interviews/28355907_1_die-hard-fan-tinku-jiya-yamla-pagla-deewana|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=17 March 2011|date=11 January 2011}}</ref> She has completed her third Kannada film ''Prasad'', in which she plays the mother of a deaf-mute eight-year-old boy.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-01-03/news-interviews/30581563_1_deaf-mute-arjun-sarja-glam | work=The Times of India | title=Madhuri Bhattacharya is two-timing | date=3 January 2012}}</ref>
